  "prompt": "Is it possible to change names in savings a/c?",
  "response": "Yes, it is generally possible to change the name on a savings account, but the specific process can vary depending on the bank or financial institution. Common reasons for changing the name may include:\n\n1. **Marriage or Divorce**: Changing your name due to marital status.\n2. **Error Correction**: Correcting a misspelled name or other inaccuracies.\n3. **Legal Name Change**: Reflecting a change due to personal or legal reasons.\n\n### Steps typically involved in changing a name on a savings account:\n\n1. **Contact Your Bank**: Reach out to your bank\u2019s customer service or visit a local branch to inquire about the process for changing your name.\n\n2. **Documentation**: You will likely need to provide legal documents that support your name change, such as a marriage certificate, divorce decree, or court order.\n\n3. **Fill Out Forms**: You may be required to complete a form to formally request the name change.\n\n4. **Identification**: Bring valid identification (like a driver's license or passport) that reflects your new name or, if it doesn't, the documentation supporting your name change.\n\n5. **Confirmation**: After processing your request, the bank should provide confirmation of the name change.\n\nIt\u2019s always best to check with your specific bank for their requirements and procedures, as they may vary.",
